# Build Premium Dashboard Skill

## 🎯 Doel

Leer hoe je zelf premium dashboard componenten bouwt met:
- 📊 Grafieken en charts (Recharts)
- 📈 Delta indicators met percentages
- 🎨 Stats cards met trends
- 📐 Grid layouts en responsive design
- 🔄 Real-time data updates

## 📋 Prerequisites

```bash
# Installeer dependencies
npm install recharts lucide-react clsx tailwind-merge

# Of als je shadcn/ui gebruikt:
npm install @radix-ui/react-slot class-variance-authority
```

## 🚀 Stap 1: Delta Indicator Component

Efferd-style delta indicators zijn het hart van een premium dashboard:

```tsx
// src/components/delta.tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
import { TrendingUp, TrendingDown, Minus } from "lucide-react"
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge"

interface DeltaProps {
  value: number              // Percentage change (5.2, -3.1, etc.)
  variant?: "default" | "badge"
  precision?: number         // Decimal places (default: 1)
  suffix?: string            // Default: "%"
  absolute?: boolean         // Show absolute value (default: true)
}

export function Delta({
  value,
  variant = "default",
  precision = 1,
  suffix = "%",
  absolute = true
}: DeltaProps) {
  const displayValue = absolute ? Math.abs(value) : value
  const formattedValue = displayValue.toFixed(precision) + suffix

  const isPositive = value > 0
  const isNegative = value < 0
  const isNeutral = value === 0

  const Icon = isPositive ? TrendingUp : isNegative ? TrendingDown : Minus

  const colors = variant === "badge"
    ? cn(
        "gap-1 border-none tabular-nums",
        isPositive ? "bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-500" : "",
        isNegative ? "bg-red-500/10 text-red-500" : "",
        isNeutral ? "bg-muted-foreground/10 text-muted-foreground" : ""
      )
    : cn(
        "inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-xs tabular-nums",
        isPositive ? "text-emerald-600" : "",
        isNegative ? "text-rose-600" : "",
        isNeutral ? "text-muted-foreground" : ""
      )

  if (variant === "badge") {
    return (
      <Badge className={colors}>
        <Icon className="w-3 h-3" />
        {formattedValue}
      </Badge>
    )
  }

  return (
    <div className={colors}>
      <Icon className="w-3 h-3" />
      <span className="tabular-nums">{formattedValue}</span>
    </div>
  )
}
```

**Gebruik:**
```tsx
<Delta value={5.2} />           // +5.2% (groen)
<Delta value={-3.1} />          // -3.1% (rood)
<Delta value={0} />             // 0% (grijs)
<Delta value={8.5} variant="badge" />  // Badge style
```

## 📊 Stap 2: Stats Card Component

Premium stats cards zoals Efferd:

```tsx
// src/components/stats-card.tsx
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card"
import { Delta } from "./delta"

interface StatProps {
  label: string
  value: string | number
  delta?: number
  footnote?: string
  lowerIsBetter?: boolean  // true = rood bij positieve delta (bijv. response time)
}

export function StatCard({
  label,
  value,
  delta,
  footnote,
  lowerIsBetter = false
}: StatProps) {
  // Als lowerIsBetter true is, flip de delta voor kleur coding
  const effectiveDelta = lowerIsBetter && delta ? -delta : delta

  return (
    <Card className="shadow-none dark:ring-0">
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle className="font-normal text-muted-foreground text-xs">
          {label}
        </CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent className="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <p className="font-semibold text-2xl tabular-nums">
          {typeof value === 'number' ? value.toLocaleString() : value}
        </p>

        {delta !== undefined && (
          <div className="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs">
            <Delta value={effectiveDelta} />
            {footnote && (
              <span className="text-muted-foreground">{footnote}</span>
            )}
          </div>
        )}
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  )
}

// Stats Grid Component
interface StatsGridProps {
  stats: StatProps[]
}

export function StatsGrid({ stats }: StatsGridProps) {
  return (
    <div className="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
      {stats.map((stat, index) => (
        <StatCard key={index} {...stat} />
      ))}
    </div>
  )
}
```

**Gebruik:**
```tsx
const stats = [
  { label: "Actieve leads", value: 127, delta: 8.5, footnote: "vs vorige week" },
  { label: "Response time", value: "4.1m", delta: -12.3, footnote: "vs vorige week", lowerIsBetter: true },
]

<StatsGrid stats={stats} />
```

## 📈 Stap 3: Charts met Recharts

Efferd-style charts in 3 stappen:

### 3.1 Line Chart (Trends)

```tsx
// src/components/charts/line-chart.tsx
import { LineChart, Line, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, Tooltip, ResponsiveContainer } from 'recharts'
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card"

interface LineChartProps {
  data: Array<{ name: string; value: number }>
  title: string
  color?: string
}

export function TrendChart({ data, title, color = "#3b82f6" }: LineChartProps) {
  return (
    <Card className="shadow-none">
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle className="text-base font-bold">{title}</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={200}>
          <LineChart data={data}>
            <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" className="stroke-muted" />
            <XAxis
              dataKey="name"
              className="text-xs text-muted-foreground"
              axisLine={false}
              tickLine={false}
            />
            <YAxis
              className="text-xs text-muted-foreground"
              axisLine={false}
              tickLine={false}
            />
            <Tooltip
              contentStyle={{
                backgroundColor: 'white',
                border: '1px solid #e5e7eb',
                borderRadius: '8px'
              }}
            />
            <Line
              type="monotone"
              dataKey="value"
              stroke={color}
              strokeWidth={2}
              dot={false}
            />
          </LineChart>
        </ResponsiveContainer>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  )
}
```

**Gebruik:**
```tsx
const weeklyData = [
  { name: 'Ma', value: 42 },
  { name: 'Di', value: 55 },
  { name: 'Wo', value: 38 },
  { name: 'Do', value: 61 },
  { name: 'Vr', value: 47 },
]

<TrendChart data={weeklyData} title="Weekly Outreach" />
```

### 3.2 Bar Chart (Categorien)

```tsx
// src/components/charts/bar-chart.tsx
import { BarChart, Bar, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, Tooltip, ResponsiveContainer } from 'recharts'

export function CategoryChart({ data, title }: { data: any[], title: string }) {
  return (
    <Card className="shadow-none">
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle className="text-base font-bold">{title}</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={200}>
          <BarChart data={data}>
            <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" className="stroke-muted" />
            <XAxis dataKey="name" className="text-xs" axisLine={false} tickLine={false} />
            <YAxis className="text-xs" axisLine={false} tickLine={false} />
            <Tooltip />
            <Bar dataKey="value" fill="#3b82f6" radius={[4, 4, 0, 0]} />
          </BarChart>
        </ResponsiveContainer>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  )
}
```

### 3.3 Area Chart (Cumulatief)

```tsx
// src/components/charts/area-chart.tsx
import { AreaChart, Area, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, Tooltip, ResponsiveContainer } from 'recharts'

export function CumulativeChart({ data, title }: { data: any[], title: string }) {
  return (
    <Card className="shadow-none">
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle className="text-base font-bold">{title}</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={200}>
          <AreaChart data={data}>
            <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" className="stroke-muted" />
            <XAxis dataKey="name" className="text-xs" axisLine={false} tickLine={false} />
            <YAxis className="text-xs" axisLine={false} tickLine={false} />
            <Tooltip />
            <Area
              type="monotone"
              dataKey="value"
              stroke="#8b5cf6"
              fill="#8b5cf6"
              fillOpacity={0.2}
            />
          </AreaChart>
        </ResponsiveContainer>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  )
}
```

## 🎨 Stap 4: Dashboard Layout

Premium grid layout zoals Efferd:

```tsx
// src/components/dashboard-layout.tsx
import { StatsGrid } from "./stats-card"
import { TrendChart } from "./charts/line-chart"
import { CategoryChart } from "./charts/bar-chart"

export function DashboardLayout() {
  // Stats data
  const stats = [
    { label: "Actieve leads", value: 127, delta: 8.5, footnote: "vs vorige week" },
    { label: "Hot leads", value: 43, delta: 5.2, footnote: "vs vorige week" },
    { label: "Response time", value: "4.1m", delta: -12.3, footnote: "vs vorige week", lowerIsBetter: true },
    { label: "Conversie", value: "12.3%", delta: 2.1, footnote: "vs vorige week" },
  ]

  // Chart data
  const weeklyData = [
    { name: 'Ma', value: 42 },
    { name: 'Di', value: 55 },
    { name: 'Wo', value: 38 },
    { name: 'Do', value: 61 },
    { name: 'Vr', value: 47 },
  ]

  const categoryData = [
    { name: 'Email', value: 45 },
    { name: 'Phone', value: 23 },
    { name: 'Social', value: 18 },
    { name: 'Referral', value: 14 },
  ]

  return (
    <div className="p-8 max-w-[1440px] mx-auto space-y-6">
      {/* Stats Grid */}
      <StatsGrid stats={stats} />

      {/* Charts Grid */}
      <div className="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <TrendChart data={weeklyData} title="Weekly Outreach" />
        <CategoryChart data={categoryData} title="Lead Sources" />
      </div>
    </div>
  )
}
```

## 🔄 Stap 5: Real-time Data Updates

```tsx
// src/components/live-dashboard.tsx
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react'

export function LiveDashboard() {
  const [stats, setStats] = useState([])
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true)

  useEffect(() => {
    // Fetch data van API
    async function fetchData() {
      try {
        const response = await fetch('/api/dashboard-stats')
        const data = await response.json()
        setStats(data)
      } catch (error) {
        console.error('Error fetching dashboard data:', error)
      } finally {
        setLoading(false)
      }
    }

    fetchData()

    // Update elke 30 seconden
    const interval = setInterval(fetchData, 30000)
    return () => clearInterval(interval)
  }, [])

  if (loading) {
    return <div>Loading dashboard...</div>
  }

  return <DashboardLayout />
}
```

## 🎯 Stap 6: Compleet Voorbeeld Dashboard

```tsx
// src/App.jsx
import { StatsGrid } from "@/components/stats-card"
import { TrendChart } from "@/components/charts/line-chart"
import { CategoryChart } from "@/components/charts/bar-chart"

function App() {
  // Brevo/CRM data
  const stats = [
    { label: "Lead kwaliteit", value: "78%", delta: 2.5, footnote: "vs vorige week" },
    { label: "Actieve leads", value: 127, delta: 8.1, footnote: "vs vorige week" },
    { label: "Hot leads", value: 43, delta: 5.2, footnote: "vs vorige week" },
    { label: "Actie nodig", value: 12, delta: -3.1, footnote: "vs gisteren", lowerIsBetter: true },
  ]

  const weeklyOutreach = [
    { name: 'Ma', value: 42, replies: 6, hot: 2 },
    { name: 'Di', value: 55, replies: 8, hot: 3 },
    { name: 'Wo', value: 38, replies: 5, hot: 2 },
    { name: 'Do', value: 61, replies: 10, hot: 4 },
    { name: 'Vr', value: 47, replies: 7, hot: 3 },
  ]

  const leadSources = [
    { name: 'Email', value: 45 },
    { name: 'LinkedIn', value: 23 },
    { name: 'Website', value: 18 },
    { name: 'Referrals', value: 14 },
  ]

  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-neutral-50">
      <div className="p-8 max-w-[1440px] mx-auto space-y-6">
        {/* Header */}
        <div className="flex justify-between items-end">
          <div>
            <h1 className="text-3xl font-bold">Dashboard</h1>
            <p className="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-600">
              Real-time lead metrics en analytics
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Stats */}
        <StatsGrid stats={stats} />

        {/* Charts */}
        <div className="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <TrendChart data={weeklyOutreach} title="Weekly Outreach" color="#3b82f6" />
          <CategoryChart data={leadSources} title="Lead Sources" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  )
}

export default App
```

## 🔧 Stap 7: Custom Styling

Efferd-style rounded cards:

```css
/* globals.css */
.dashboard-card {
  @apply rounded-[28px] border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-none;
}

.dashboard-card:hover {
  @apply shadow-sm transition-shadow;
}
```

Of inline:
```tsx
<Card className="rounded-[28px] border-neutral-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-none">
```

## 📊 Chart Types Overview

| Chart Type | Use Case | Recharts Component |
|-----------|----------|-------------------|
| **Line** | Trends over tijd | `<LineChart>` |
| **Bar** | Categorien vergelijken | `<BarChart>` |
| **Area** | Cumulatieve data | `<AreaChart>` |
| **Pie** | Percentages verdeling | `<PieChart>` |
| **Scatter** | Correlaties | `<ScatterChart>` |

## 🎨 Kleur Schemas

```tsx
const colors = {
  primary: "#3b82f6",    // Blauw
  success: "#10b981",    // Groen (positive delta)
  danger: "#ef4444",     // Rood (negative delta)
  warning: "#f59e0b",    // Oranje (hot leads)
  neutral: "#6b7280",    // Grijs (neutral)
}
```

## 🚀 Next Steps

1. **Installeer Recharts**: `npm install recharts`
2. **Kopieer components**: Delta, StatsCard, Charts
3. **Voeg je data toe**: Brevo, CRM, of API
4. **Customize styling**: Kleuren, fonts, spacing
5. **Test responsiveness**: Mobile vs desktop layouts

## 💡 Pro Tips

- **Gebruik `tabular-nums`** voor betere nummer alignment
- **Rounded corners**: `rounded-[28px]` voor premium look
- **Delta colors**: Rood = slecht (meestal), Groen = goed
- **LowerIsBetter**: Voor metrics zoals response time
- **Grid layouts**: `grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4`
- **Chart heights**: 200-300px voor beste resultaten

